<subSubSection id="903662993471B878C02D72BBA059FCE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3BC6F491399B98AC682E46465CB28671" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="01DD002253377696282BE884748A6112" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
A species of 
<taxonomicName id="CC66501B9F98CED9663FBBB2509DE959" authorityName="P.J.Miller &amp; Wongrat" authorityYear="1979" class="Pisces" family="Gobiidae" genus="Egglestonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Egglestonichthys" order="Perciformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AF8DADEAF266FA7C9943C2A236D80AC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Egglestonichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5CCB229E41CF4F5C3FBFD917E3E27F3B" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Holotype of Egglestonichthys fulmen sp. nov., OMNH-P 43993, 21.7 mm SL, Okinawa Island, Ryukyu Islands, Japan A fresh Fresh coloration B preserved Fresh coloration C radiograph." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1006.58874.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489531" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">1</figureCitation>
) with the following combination of characters: anal-fin rays I, 9; pectoral-fin rays 17, lower rays connected by membrane; longitudinal series scales 25; transverse scales 8; pre-dorsal-fin scale rows 8; cheek and opercle naked (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D79CE5A6C8EAB42F39C5C8D9E1D9C82C" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sketches of head region of Egglestonichthys fulmen sp. nov. based on OMNH-P 43993, holotype, 21.7 mm SL. Note that sensory papillae have been abraded during capture A dorsal view B lateral view C ventral view. AN and PN indicate anterior and posterior nostrils, respectively. Arrowheads indicate anteroventral end of gill opening. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1006.58874.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489532" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">2B</figureCitation>
); pelvic frenum absent; caudal fin lanceolate, its length 32.2% of SL; interorbital width very narrow, 1.2% of HL (much narrower than pupil diameter) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2314162B8BA6A07A1ED5C4EBBE20F13B" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Sketches of head region of Egglestonichthys fulmen sp. nov. based on OMNH-P 43993, holotype, 21.7 mm SL. Note that sensory papillae have been abraded during capture A dorsal view B lateral view C ventral view. AN and PN indicate anterior and posterior nostrils, respectively. Arrowheads indicate anteroventral end of gill opening. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1006.58874.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489532" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">2A</figureCitation>
); no spicules or odontoid processes on outer surface of gill arches; and body whitish, upper half with broken zigzag pattern of bright yellow patches and associated scattered black melanophores in fresh specimens (melanophores retained in preserved specimens) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1E92C91E7E612BEEDD0C31E79A8BEBD2" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Holotype of Egglestonichthys fulmen sp. nov., OMNH-P 43993, 21.7 mm SL, Okinawa Island, Ryukyu Islands, Japan A fresh Fresh coloration B preserved Fresh coloration C radiograph." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1006.58874.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489531" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">1A, B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="7C9CD459C835AC2CB26A128A4999E54E" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1006.58874.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489531" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
